IRS990.MissionDesc: SINCE ITS ORIGIN IN 1934, THE MISSION OF THE DETROIT ECONOMIC CLUB (DEC) HAS BEEN TO PROVIDE A PLATFORM FOR THE DEBATE AND DISCUSSION OF THE GREAT BUSINESS, GOVERNMENT AND SOCIAL ISSUES OF THE DAY.
IRS990.Desc: SPEAKER MEETINGS: THESE MEETINGS WERE MOSTLY HELD IN-PERSON, WITH A HANDFUL OF VIRTUAL EVENTS. SPEAKERS INCLUDED CEOS, GOVERNMENT OFFICIALS, AND AUTHORS. MEETINGS PROVIDE A PLATFORM FOR THE DISCUSSION AND DEBATE OF IMPORTANT BUSINESS, GOVERNMENT AND SOCIAL ISSUES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CLUB IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL INCOME TAX UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE EXCEPT FOR NET INCOME DERIVED FROM UNRELATED BUSINESS ACTIVITIES. THE TAX EFFECTS FROM AN UNCERTAIN TAX POSITION CAN BE RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, ONLY IF THE POSITION IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT TO BE SUSTAINED ON AUDIT, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. THE CLUB RECOGNIZES THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT BENEFIT OF A TAX POSITION ONLY AFTER DETERMINING THAT THE RELEVANT TAX AUTHORITY WOULD MORE LIKELY THAN NOT SUSTAIN THE POSITION FOLLOWING AN AUDIT. FOR TAX POSITIONS MEETING THE MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THRESHOLD, THE AMOUNT RECOGNIZED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS IS THE LARGEST BENEFIT THAT HAS A GREATER THAN 50% LIKELIHOOD OF BEING REALIZED, UPON ULTIMATE SETTLEMENT WITH THE RELEVANT TAX AUTHORITY. AT JUNE 30, 2022 AND 2021, THERE WERE NO UNCERTAIN TAX PROVISIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PRESIDENT/CEO'S COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD, MEMBERS OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE, AND THE CLUB'S TREASURER. COMPENSATION IS ALSO PARTIALLY BASED UPON COMPARABILITY DATA FROM OTHER SIMILAR SIZED 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATIONS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON WRITTEN OR VERBAL REQUEST. THE REQUESTS ARE GIVEN TO THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE AND ADMINISTRATION FOR PROCESSING AND DOCUMENTS MAY BE E-MAILED, FAXED, OR MAILED TO THE REQUESTOR. THERE MAY BE A NOMINAL FEE CHARGED TO THE REQUESTOR IF THE DOCUMENTS ARE MAILED.
THE CLUB HAS NOT CHANGED ITS OVERSIGHT OR SELECTION PROCESS OF AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTANT DURING THE TAX YEAR.
